NO COPIED PROPRIETARY CODE OR DATA
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This repository contains no proprietary third-party material. In
particular, the following categories of material are NOT included
in this repository and have not been used in its authorship:

  * Vehicle manufacturer firmware images (ECU flash binaries,
    bootloader images, calibration maps, partition tables, etc.)
  * Decompiled or disassembled output of any vehicle manufacturer
    software or firmware
  * Cryptographic material (signing keys, session seeds,
    certificates, private keys, authentication secrets)
  * Commercial diagnostic software (ISTA, E-Sys, WinKFP, INPA,
    ESYSX, ICOM firmware, or any variant) — neither bundled,
    mirrored, nor extracted
  * Third-party tuning software, maps, tables, or calibration data
  * Copyrighted protocol documentation from any OEM, Tier 1
    supplier, or standards body beyond what is publicly available
    under open-access terms
  * Any data obtained through unauthorized access to any system

All protocol knowledge encoded in this project was derived from:

  * Public standards documents (ISO 14229 UDS, ISO 13400 DoIP,
    ISO 15765 ISO-TP, ISO 3779 VIN structure)
  * Publicly published academic security research (conference
    papers, journal articles, thesis work)
  * Publicly available open-source protocol dissectors (notably
    Scapy's automotive contribs and Wireshark's HSFZ dissector)
  * Observation of the author's own vehicles on private bench
    networks, documented under the authorized-use terms in
    DISCLAIMER.md and SCOPE.md

